Read and Parse REDCap Data Dictionary

read_and_parse_dict.Rd

This function reads a REDCap data dictionary (CSV format) and parses the "Choices" column to create a named list of value-label pairs for use in data recoding. If the field is "country", a special parser allows both country codes and names to map to values.

Usage

read_and_parse_dict(dictPath)

Arguments

dictPath

Path to the REDCap data dictionary CSV file.

Value

A named list of named vectors, where each list element corresponds to a field name, and each named vector maps value codes to human-readable labels.

Examples

dicts <- read_and_parse_dict("data_dictionary.csv")
#> Warning: cannot open file 'data_dictionary.csv': No such file or directory
#> Error in file(file, "rt"): cannot open the connection
dicts[["sample_buffer"]]
#> Error: object 'dicts' not found
# > Glycerol-saline = Glycerol-saline
# > RNAshield = RNAshield
# > ...
